The paper deals with algorithms for solving flow problems in graphs, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The techniques used in the paper involve graph sparsification, oblivious routing, and non-Euclidean gradient descent, which are all relevant to the areas of data structures, network optimization, discrete mathematics, computational geometry, and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
